Noemi Romano

loving everything at the intersection

A new island in Venice

EPFL, Feb 2015 - Jun 2015

During the course of Visualizing future cities: Venice @ EPFL we had the opportunity to rethink the Venice of the future. Mass tourism, souvenir shops, restaurants, but where is the city and where are the Venetians? Dating all the way back to the city's original charter, Venice is an artificial island. So, why not build a new artifical island and provide a new space for the Venetians and far away from the mass tourism?

In this project, my principal task was to visualize this new island in VR within the Oculus Rift and with the Google Street View images in the background.

Teacher: Isabella Pasqualini

In collaboration with: Laura Bornet

Technologies: Unity3D QGIS Oculus Rift Google Street View

Galeazza 3D reconstruction
